        rationale: "Hypocalcemia from citrate toxicity during massive transfusion causes refractory hypotension and cardiac dysfunction. Citrate in banked blood chelates ionized calcium. Calcium gluconate 1-2 g IV should be administered after every 4-6 units of blood products. Correcting hypocalcemia often restores cardiac contractility and vascular tone."
