    pearls: ["Missed injury rate in trauma is 1-39% — the tertiary survey (complete re-examination + imaging review within 24 hours) is essential to catch missed injuries","The 6 immediately life-threatening thoracic injuries: airway obstruction, tension pneumothorax, open pneumothorax, massive hemothorax, flail chest, cardiac tamponade","Massive hemothorax criteria for emergent thoracotomy: >1500 mL initial chest tube output OR >200 mL/hr for 2-4 hours","Pelvic binder should be placed at the level of the greater trochanters — placing it too high is ineffective; apply on clinical suspicion, do NOT repeatedly assess pelvic stability","Flail chest: the paradoxical chest wall movement is often less clinically important than the underlying pulmonary contusion, which is the primary cause of hypoxemia","Compartment syndrome is a TIME-SENSITIVE surgical emergency requiring fasciotomy within 6 hours to prevent irreversible muscle necrosis and limb loss","Log roll for posterior examination is mandatory in the secondary survey — thoracolumbar spine injuries are missed when posterior exam is omitted","Ketamine is the preferred induction agent in hemodynamically unstable trauma patients because it maintains blood pressure through catecholamine release"],
