    pearls: ["ANY fever within 3 months of return from a malaria-endemic area is MALARIA UNTIL PROVEN OTHERWISE — this is a medical emergency requiring immediate thick/thin blood smears","P. falciparum causes the most severe malaria (cerebral malaria, ARDS, severe anemia) and is dominant in SUB-SAHARAN AFRICA — prophylaxis compliance is critical for this region","Primaquine and tafenoquine are the ONLY drugs that kill P. vivax/P. ovale liver hypnozoites — MUST screen for G6PD deficiency before prescribing (hemolytic anemia in G6PD-deficient patients)","Atovaquone-proguanil (Malarone) advantages: short lead time (1-2 days before), short tail (7 days after), well-tolerated; disadvantage: expensive, daily dosing","Mefloquine advantages: weekly dosing; disadvantages: neuropsychiatric effects (vivid dreams, anxiety, psychosis), must start 2 WEEKS before travel, contraindicated in seizure disorders and psychiatric history","Traveler's diarrhea prevention: 'Boil it, cook it, peel it, or forget it' — avoid tap water, ice, raw vegetables, and street food in high-risk areas","Azithromycin is preferred over fluoroquinolones for traveler's diarrhea in South/Southeast Asia due to high rates of fluoroquinolone-resistant Campylobacter","Yellow fever vaccine is a LIVE vaccine — contraindicated in immunosuppressed patients, pregnant women, and infants <9 months; some countries REQUIRE proof of vaccination for entry"],
